{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/customize-your-rstudio-theme-914cca8b04b1", "time": 1682994279.5210419, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/customize-your-rstudio-theme-914cca8b04b1/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How to Customize your RStudio Theme (Finally) | by Brad Lindblad | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How to Customize your RStudio Theme (Finally)", "description": "Along with cruising Stack Overflow (SO), Reddit and Medium when we\u2019re bored, programmers like to fiddle with IDE themes, fonts and styles to an insane degree. It\u2019s not that our current font or color\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.rescuetime.com/", "anchor_text": "RescueTime", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://stackexchange.com/questions", "anchor_text": "Hot Network Questions", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://github.com/hadley", "anchor_text": "Hadley\u2019s", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://panda.siamak.work/", "anchor_text": "Panda syntax theme", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://github.com/kencrocken/FiraCodeiScript", "anchor_text": "excellent font put together by Ken Crocken", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://tmtheme-editor.herokuapp.com/#!/editor/theme/Monokai", "anchor_text": "online editor", "paragraph_index": 15}], "all_paragraphs": ["When my brain is tapped out after a grueling morning of data sciencing, my browser will invariably point to a smorgasbord of websites that RescueTime will classify as \u201centertainment.\u201d From the Hot Network Questions page on Stack Overflow (\u201cQuestion: why do demons heal faster than angels?\u201d) to looking into Hadley\u2019s commits for the last six months.", "After I feel like I\u2019ve seen the entire internet, I\u2019ll sometimes start fiddling with my IDE theme, as if changing the hex color of my function calls will actually improve my work. It\u2019s not that my current font or color scheme aren\u2019t perfectly fine, it\u2019s the juicy rationalization that I\u2019ll actually work faster if I have some dope ligatures.", "I reinforce my obsession with these minutia by reminding myself what Oliver Wendell Holmes said way back in the 19th century; supposedly regarding his Win95 settings:", "\u201cA moment\u2019s insight is sometimes worth a life\u2019s experience\u201d", "So maybe, all of this sharpening of the axe, so to speak, is actually beneficial. Maybe, it makes us more suseptible to positive black swans. There, that\u2019s a healthy rationalization!", "I work in RStudio a lot, and while there\u2019s been excellent themes and styles available for most IDEs and text editors like Sublime, Atom, Visual Studio Code for years, we RStudio peeps have been limited in this area. We\u2019ve had a few basic themes and that\u2019s about it.", "Welp, that all changed a few months ago. RStudio v1.2xxx Preview was released in October and has a host of new features, including:", "But for us, the sweetest feature is the ability to import our own themes! This article will quickly run through how we can duplicate the Panda syntax theme in RStudio.", "RStudio now lets you upload .tmThemes and .rsThemes files. I hacked together a Panda-like theme and put it in a repo for you to download. I\u2019ve also included an awesome font called \u201cFira Code iScript\u201d in the repo, which we\u2019ll get to later. Download the files with this git command:", "Fira Code iScript is an excellent font put together by Ken Crocken which is a mash up of Fira Code and Script12. This font applies the Script12 typeface wherever there are italics, and Fira code everywhere else. To install it, double click on the .tff files you downloaded and then install the fonts in your system, which will be different for each OS.", "It will end up looking like this:", "Pretty cool, eh? To use this font in RStudio, follow these steps:", "Note that you can install pretty much any font you want by following this process.", "Next we\u2019ll install the panda theme. Follow along:", "Now all you need is a quick restart and you\u2019re rocking a new sweet theme! This is what it looks like in my system (Linux Mint 19, Dark):", "If the panda theme doesn\u2019t do it for you, you can make your own with this online editor. This allows you to make any kind of custom theme you want. You just need to download the theme from the website and upload it to RStudio like we did above.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "I do data science, machine learning, fly drones, paint and write."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F914cca8b04b1&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcustomize-your-rstudio-theme-914cca8b04b1&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcustomize-your-rstudio-theme-914cca8b04b1&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcustomize-your-rstudio-theme-914cca8b04b1&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-------